# No Dead Code

## ECharts Only — No Plotly Remnants

ECharts replaced Plotly completely. Do not add or restore Plotly-era code:

```js
// ❌ Dead Plotly patterns — remove on sight
sampleData(figure)
sanitizeLayout(layout)
DEFAULT_LAYOUT
DEFAULT_COLORS
trace.x / trace.y          // Plotly trace structure
paper_bgcolor / plot_bgcolor  // Plotly layout keys
```

All chart options must use the ECharts format (`series`, `xAxis`, `yAxis`, `legend`, etc.).

## No Rollback Comments

Use git history for rollback — do not leave commented-out code with rollback annotations:

```js
// ❌
// import AgentChatPanel from './AgentChatPanel'; // kept for rollback
// const [showOldPanel, setShowOldPanel] = useState(false);
```

If an import is commented out, delete it. If a component is not rendered anywhere, delete it (or properly archive it in git).

## No Debug-Only Listeners or Logs in Production Components

```js
// ❌ Debug listener left in EChartsWrapper that only console.logs
chart.getZr().on('click', (params) => {
  console.log('ZRender click:', params); // never used for real functionality
});
```

Event listeners must drive real behaviour. Remove any that only log.

## No CORS Toggles Hardcoded in Source

```python
# ❌ Development toggle left in production code
# allow_origins=["*"]   ← commented out but visible in app.py
allow_origins=[os.getenv("ALLOWED_ORIGINS", "http://localhost:3000")]
```

Use environment variables for origin configuration. Do not leave commented wildcard origins.

## Shared Utilities — No Duplication

Utility functions used in more than one file belong in `src/lib/utils.js`:

```js
// ❌ Defined in both App.jsx and echartsRegistry.js
function truncateText(text, maxLength = 20) { ... }

// ✅ Define once, import everywhere
import { truncateText } from '../../lib/utils';
```

Before adding a utility function, check if it already exists in `src/lib/utils.js`.
